Package org.apache.flex.compiler.exceptions

This package contains classes representing custom Java exceptions that may be thrown by the compiler.

See: Description

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BuildCanceledException
    This exception is thrown when the build of a target is canceled
    BURMAbortException
    A BURMAbortException terminates a BURM and signals the code generator that the BURM's results are not valid.
    CircularDependencyException
    Exception thrown when a graph is found to contain a circular dependency.
    CodegenInterruptedException
    When an InterruptedException is thrown during codegen, wrap it in a RuntimeException and catch it higher up.
    ConfigurationException
    A common base class for configuration related exceptions.

    DuplicateLabelException
    Checked exception thrown by the control-flow management logic when a new label duplicates an active label.
    LibraryCircularDependencyException
    Exception thrown when a LibraryDependencyGraph is sorted and found to form a circular dependency.
    MissingBuiltinException
    MissingBuiltinException signals name resolution clients that the builtin types are not available, and the result of any compilation should be viewed with extreme skepticism.
    UnknownControlFlowTargetException
    Checked exception thrown by the control-flow management logic when a requested control-flow target cannot be found.

Package org.apache.flex.compiler.exceptions Description

This package contains classes representing custom Java exceptions that may be thrown by the compiler.
